<div id="review_2376615783" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2376615783" />
    <a title="Salem Reid" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/68753774-salem-reid"><img alt="Salem Reid" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1606758445p2/68753774.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2376615783?book_show_action=true">Jan 22, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Salem Reid" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Salem Reid" href="/user/show/68753774-salem-reid">Salem Reid</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2376615783" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13419700510745861980">So Hard To Say is a cute short story about two characters in turn-style POVs. We have Xio whose met this new kid and falls for him while dealing with the fact that her father has left their family and she doesn&apos;t know why. And we have Frederick, who can&apos;t figure out why he doesn&apos;t like Xio and why he likes someone else instead.<br/><br/>I liked seeing the different cultures represented in the story and I adore the young writing Sanchez has, it brings me back to when I was just as young and figuring things</span>
  <span id="freeText13419700510745861980" style="display:none">So Hard To Say is a cute short story about two characters in turn-style POVs. We have Xio whose met this new kid and falls for him while dealing with the fact that her father has left their family and she doesn't know why. And we have Frederick, who can't figure out why he doesn't like Xio and why he likes someone else instead.<br /><br />I liked seeing the different cultures represented in the story and I adore the young writing Sanchez has, it brings me back to when I was just as young and figuring things out! <br /><br />There was, needless to say a lot of drama! I adored the characters and their roles and I loved how involved family was throughout the story. It was very touching! <br /><br />All in all I'm glad they all had a happy ending- albeit cut short ( I definitely could have done with a few more pages to see what changed next ) and I thought it was a fun read! I definitely recommend it for everyone!</span>
  <a data-text-id="13419700510745861980" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


