              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9062700098364567755">I bailed early on this one. I work in a middle school setting and, to me, the way these characters all talked and behaved was much more like High School than 8th grade. Too many things didn’t feel authentic. For example, after establishing that the male lead is one of the shorter boys in the school, he winds up being put into a pick up game of soccer as a goalie and he does pretty well despite playing against a bunch of guys who play a lot together. </span>

          </span>
